Kisii county commissioner Karanja Njora on Monday warned politicians against hate speech.Njora said the government will not sit back and watch leaders incite people against each other to gain political mileage.He said it will be prudent for leaders to dwell on selling development policies to the electorate, not insulting each other.The commissioner called for respect on leaders who are in office.Njora spoke at the Gusii Stadium during Jamhuri Day celebrations, which were officiated by Governor James Ongwae.He said the administration will not fear anybody, adding that those found engaging in hate speech will be arrested and charged.Ongwae said he will not engage in activities meant to divide people as the country approaches the general elections.